      "name": "Hemolysis index validation at 5 L/min nominal flow",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 L/min, 2500 RPM. Predicted NIH = 0.0041 g/100 L; measured NIH = 0.0038 ± 0.0006 g/100 L. Agreement within 8%. Monte Carlo sampling over blood viscosity and inlet velocity distributions is described in the accompanying simulation report; however, no formal UQ artifact is linked to this result record. Aleatory variability in RBC fragility across donor samples contributes an uncharacterized spread in the experimental reference values.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/monte-carlo-vad-5lpm"
    },
