      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation at 3000 RPM elevated speed",
      "description": "CFD-predicted NIH compared against in-vitro measurements at 4 L/min, 3000 RPM operating point. Predicted NIH = 0.0089 g/100 L; measured NIH = 0.0094 ± 0.0012 g/100 L. Relative error 5.3%. Uncertainty in shear-stress exposure time distributions is discussed qualitatively in the validation report narrative, noting that donor-to-donor RBC fragility variation introduces aleatory uncertainty estimated informally at ±15% on the hemolysis scalar. No structured UQ artifact is attached to this result; the prose acknowledgement does not constitute a linked quantification.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/monte-carlo-vad-3000rpm"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-low-flow-3lpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation at low-flow 3 L/min condition",
      "description": "CFD-predicted NIH at 3 L/min, 2800 RPM compared against in-vitro data. Predicted NIH = 0.0062 g/100 L; measured NIH = 0.0058 ± 0.0009 g/100 L. Agreement within 7%. The simulation report notes that hematocrit variability (±3% absolute) and temperature fluctuations during in-vitro testing contribute aleatory uncertainty to the reference measurements. These sources are described in prose but no Monte Carlo or interval-based UQ artifact is linked to this validation result record. Aleatory uncertainty therefore remains uncharacterized at the result level."
    },
