      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis threshold; secondary QoIs (shear stress, exposure time) demonstrated relevant to hemolysis prediction mechanism.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary clinical QoI and directly compared against the absolute threshold. Shear stress and exposure time distributions used as intermediate QoIs in the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model. Mapping from intermediate to clinical QoI validated at simplified geometry level only. Achieved level 3."
